               <head>Unidentified commentary on Rumi’s Masnavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010113603 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1052-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled commentary by an unidentified commentator on the 
                <title key="work_22905">Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title>of 
                <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">"Rūmī" Mawlānā Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad Bahāʾ al-Dīn Valad Balkhī</persName>(d. 670/1271).
                        </p>
                        <p>The volume is significantly defective at beginning.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 184v): completed at night, ghurrah (=1) of Rabīʿ al-S̲ānī (year not entered). Datable to the early to mid-nineteenth century.</p>
                        <p>Rough nastaʿlīq tending to shikastah āmīz on coarse paper.</p>
                        <p>Folios severely cropped; wormholes toward the centre; stains, tears.</p>
                        <p>Annotations.</p>
                        <p>Boards of present binding brittle and cracked (polychrome decoratively printed paper edged with brown leather). Pencil note on inside of front flap: Rejected 18 Jan 1904.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
